<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Howl2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Howl,</orth> vb) 1) to cry as a wolf: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.288" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 288</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.119" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 2, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.7.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 7, 63</bibl>. as a dog: <bibl n="shak. ven 918" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 918</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 277" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 277</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.240" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 240</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.3.100" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 3, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.4.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 4, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 6, 46</bibl>. Used of bad singers: <cit><quote>a --ing monster,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 183</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 82</bibl>.<lb />2) to cry in anguish: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 1, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.296" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 296</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.233.296" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 233</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 3, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.257" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 257</bibl>. With <emph>out,</emph> tr.: <cit><quote>words that would be --ed out in the desert air,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.194" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 194</bibl></cit>. Used of those suffering the pains of hell: <cit><quote>for the which I think thou wilt h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.374" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 374</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>when thou liest --ing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.265" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 265</bibl></cit>. Of fiends: <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.59" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 59</bibl>. <emph>--ing,</emph> quite substantively: <cit><quote>the damned use that word in hell; --ings attend it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 3, 48</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>